Maintainer: Nima Hejazi <nh@nimahejazi.org>
Description: Targeted maximum likelihood (TML) estimation of population-level
    causal mediation effects defined by static or stochastic interventions. The
    causal effects for which targeted doubly robust estimators are provided
    include the controlled direct effect, the natural (in)direct effects, and
    the population intervention (in)direct effects.
